		<title>02SOUTHMOOR HOSPITAL</title>
		<content> This used to be called HOLMSIDE and   
 SOUTHMOOR MINERS WELFARE HOSPITAL.It  
 was built in 1927 and the miners paid 
 3 pence(3d) a week from their wages to
 help pay for it.It was handed over to 
 the NATIONAL HEALTH SERVICE in 1948.  
 The hospital has 38 beds split into 4 
 wards and it is now becoming a        
 geriatric hopital.It used to have an  
 operating theatre but it closed down  
 in May 1985.It has a very busy        
 Out_patients Department which handles 
 about 1000 people a month.            
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
